    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable per ASME V&V 40 Table 1 at MRL 2. CFD predictions of NIH are within 25% of experimental measurements across all 5 operating points, and the worst-case hemolysis condition is correctly identified. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is satisfied relative to the predicate device. The overall credibility of the CFD model is sufficient to support the intended use decision for the Class II CPB device.",
